      • getSearchResult

        public java.util.ArrayList<JetstarFlight> getSearchResult​(int index)
                                                   throws java.lang.Exception
        This returns a list of available flights for a specified searching flight.
        Parameters:
        index - The index of the searching flight. For example, flights "MEL to ADL" and "ADL to MEL" have been provided via the inputFlight function. The index of "MEL to ADL" is 0 and the index of "ADL to MEL" is 1.
        Returns:
        A list of available flights.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - Throw an exception message if the method is called in an incorrect state.
